# Expected output markers for prompt-builder: tool-calling-agent scenario
# Two line formats:
#   CHECK_ID  SEVERITY  VERDICT        — grep for self-review verdicts (e.g. [O-7] ... PASS)
#   @PATTERN|SEVERITY|PRESENT         — grep for structural presence in generated code/prompt

# ── Self-review verdicts (Phase 3 output) ─────────────────────────────────
O-7   CRITICAL  PASS   # Structured prompt separation
O-8   HIGH      PASS   # System prompt security rules
O-11  CRITICAL  PASS   # Output validation exists
O-16  CRITICAL  PASS   # LLM output not directly executed (parameterized SQL only)
O-17  HIGH      PASS   # Least privilege (read-only DB, tool allowlist)
O-18  CRITICAL  PASS   # Human approval for destructive actions
O-20  MEDIUM    PASS   # Rate limiting
O-21  HIGH      PASS   # Structured logging

# ── Structural markers in generated prompt ────────────────────────────────
@USER_DATA_TO_PROCESS|CRITICAL|PRESENT
@NOT instructions to follow|CRITICAL|PRESENT
@NEVER reveal|HIGH|PRESENT
# O-8 security rule 2: data/command separation — "DATA ... never as instructions" or "DATA, not instructions"
@DATA.*instructions|HIGH|PRESENT
# O-8: tool-calling variant must add "request don't execute" rule — "may REQUEST actions" or similar
@may REQUEST.*actions|HIGH|PRESENT

# ── Tool-calling-specific markers (O-16, O-17, O-18, M-6, M-7, M-8) ─────
# Human-in-the-loop function: LLM can request, not execute (O-18, M-7)
@request_human_review|CRITICAL|PRESENT
# Table allowlist: scoped tool access (O-17, M-6) — accepts ALLOWED_TABLES or ALLOWED_READ_TABLES
@ALLOWED_.*TABLE|HIGH|PRESENT
# Parameterized SQL or SELECT allowlist (O-16, M-8)
@SELECT|HIGH|PRESENT

# ── Base structural markers in generated code ─────────────────────────────
@InputGuardrail|CRITICAL|PRESENT
@OutputGuardrail|CRITICAL|PRESENT
@rate_limit|HIGH|PRESENT
@security_log|HIGH|PRESENT
@INJECTION_PATTERNS|HIGH|PRESENT
@decode_obfuscation|HIGH|PRESENT
